VP. SURYA RAOThanks to the Tirumala Tirupathi Devasthanam's Annamacharya Project, some hundreds of great compositions of the `Sankeertana Pitamaha' Annamacharya have now reached even the layman.Vidwans are also propagating thekeertanasthrough their concerts.Pappu Sadasiva Sastri of Vijayawada, a dedicated and devoted singer of Annamacharyakeertanas,particularly has been singing thekeertanasin various temples and Sabhas regularly contributing in no small measure in popularising the compositions.In a recent concert held in Kodanda Ramalayam, Sadasiva Sastri treated the lovers of devotional music with his highly appealing presentation of a large number of Annamayyakeertanas&#151;  some already heard and some new.Some of the fine renditions includedAbhayanayakudu(Bouli),Deva Namo Deva(Hamsadhwani),Anisamu Talacharo(Natakuranji),Kandarpa Janaka(Valaji),Bhavamulona(Sudha Dhanyasi),Akativelala(Subhali),Muddugare Yasoda(Kuranji),Periginadu Choodaro(Mohana) and many more compositions.Sastri was well accompanied by G. Srinivasamurthy on violin and Jayaraj ontabla.Bottom Template Starts
